Breast Cancer Classification using Principal Component Analysis (PCA) and Support Vector Machine (SVM)

Objective:
Develop a machine learning pipeline for breast cancer diagnosis by reducing feature dimensionality with PCA and classifying tumors using SVM.

Methods:
- Data Preprocessing
- Feature Standardization
- Principal Component Analysis (PCA)
- Explained Variance Analysis
- Support Vector Machine (SVM) Classification
- Model Evaluation using Accuracy, Precision, Recall, and F1-Score

Results:
- Reduced 30 original features into principal components
- Retained approximately 95% of data variance
- Improved computational efficiency
- Achieved accurate classification of malignant and benign tumors
